rComments: He is so sweet and a fair professor. He might be a bit old and dry when lecturing on content, but if you actually try to make use of the 2hours you're there by paying attention, lectures aren't that painful. Get your hands on old tests. Extremely hard marker. He expects an essay for each question on his exams - intro, body, and conclusion. His teaching methods are out of date. He literally sat at the front of the class and spent the two hours reading off his hand written notes.

rComments: Hard marker. Uses extremely outdated teaching and testing methods that do not reflect your true knowledge. Be prepared to lose lots of marks on tests just because you don't fit with his teaching and testing style.

Ian Brown may not be the most interesting lecturer, but he is able to explain concepts clearly and concisely. The final exam isn't cumulative and only covers 5 lectures. The midterm and final exam were extremely fair in terms of content. HOWEVER, the marking was pretty tough- only because the TA was looking for very specific phrases/wording.
As mentioned by others, lectures were boring. Be prepared to write pages on the exam!
Bad teaching style; basically just read off slides and notes. Not very helpful.
